div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division.
In the matter of the application of Ng Key Tung, for a writ of Habeas Corpus.
The President of the United States of America, to U. S. Commissioner of Immigration White:

We command you that you have the body of Ng Key Tung, by you imprisoned and detained under order of deportation as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention and order of deportation by whatsoever name the said Ng Key Tung shall be named or charged, before Honorable Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the United States District Court for teh Western District of Washington, Northern Division, at the Federal Building in Seattle, State of Washington, on the 5th day of NovemberDec, 1914, at 10 o'clock, aM. of that date, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Ng Key Tung and have you then and there the body of the said Ng Key Tung and there this writ.

Witness: the Honorable Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the Unied States District Court, Western District of Washington, Northern Division, at the Federal Building, Seattle, Washington, this 17 day of November, 1914.
ATTEST, my hand and seal of the United States District Court, the day and year last above written.
div1.ab:
FRANK L. CROSBY
Clerk By Ed M Lakin
Deputy Clerk.
div1.p: United States of America, Western DISTRICT OF Washington} ss:

I hereby certify and return that I served the annexed writ of Habeas Corpus on the therein-named Henry D White U S Immigration Commisioner
by handing to and leaving a true and correct thereof with him personally at Seattle Wash in said District on the 17th day of November, A. D. 1914
div1.ab:
John M Boyle
U. S. Marshal. By Will D Downey
Deputy.
